history.content: Yes. UGBA 10 may require attendance in ways that CS 61A does not (since you can watch webcast lectures). To block enrollment both courses would have to disallow time conflicts. Note that faculty are not responsible for providing alternate exam times for finals and if UGBA 10 has a final exam it would likely conflict with 61A's since the lectures do have this conflict.  Students are responsible for making sure that this could be accommodated by alternate exam times provided by course teaching staff. If that isn't going to happen, then --even though the system will allow you to enroll in both-- you shouldn't since otherwise you will have no option but to fail one of the exams since you won't be able to take both.

Hello, 

I have two classes that are in time conflict. One class allows for time conflict (cs 61a) but the other does not (ugba 10). Can i still sign up for both? 

Thanks!
history.subject: Time conflict
